# Keep build context small + free of local-machine artifacts.
#
# Why this exists: chat-chart's render_local.py was being executed during
# local smoke tests on macOS, which created an `__pycache__/` next to it
# (Python's bytecode cache, tied to the dev machine's Python version). That
# directory got COPYed into the Docker image at /opt/psd-skills/chat-chart/,
# carrying macOS extended attributes (com.apple.provenance, etc.) into the
# layer. AgentCore's snapshotter failed to mount the resulting overlay
# ("Failed to mount overlay: No such file or directory") and every microVM
# boot failed. Ignoring these patterns at build time keeps the image
# byte-clean regardless of what the developer did locally.

# Python bytecode caches
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# Node-side scratch
node_modules/

# macOS Finder metadata
.DS_Store
*.icloud

# Editor / IDE noise
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp

# Build-time eval-gate probe artifacts (issue #1161) — trend data, not image content
.build-probes/

# Local-only test scratch
test_*.py
*.test.ts
*.test.js
mcp-test-support.js
